article.headline: Detroit 78, Chicago St. 68
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Ryvon Covile scored 19 points and grabbed nine rebounds Monday to lead Detroit to a 78-68 win over Chicago State. Detroit (8-13) shot nearly 50 percent from the floor in the first half, while holding Chicago State to 10-of-26 shooting. However, the Cougars made six of 12 3-point attempts to make the score 34-30 at the half. Detroit was holding a 65-54 lead with 8:00 left when they went on a 10-0 run to put the game out of reach of the Cougars (8-17), who were playing only their fourth home game of the season. Jon Goode finished the contest with 17 points for the Titans, Brandon Cotton had 15 and Nemanja Jokic added a career-high 10 points. David Holston was the leading scorer for Chicago State with 23 points. Royce Parran scored 18 points, and Aaron Williams added 12.
